HEADWORD: Prakrit
<hw>Pra"krit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.
<ets>pr⟦amac⟧k⟦rsdot⟧ta</ets> original, natural, usual, common,
vulgar.]</ety> <def>Any one of the popular dialects descended from, or
akin to, Sanskrit; -- in distinction from the Sanskrit, which was used
as a literary and learned language when no longer spoken by the people.
Pali is one of the <ex>Prakrit</ex> dialects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

